user-preference-first.usertext:
Current task: {task_description}

Items JSON (includes all attributes; IDs are for internal reasoning only — do not show IDs to the user):
{items_block}

Known ambiguities or missing info:
{ambiguity_info}

Generate ONE high-level question to clarify preferences or desired organization principles that would best guide subsequent actions. Keep it concise and avoid repeating known information.

Return both your reasoning and the specific question in English.

parallel-exploration.usertext:
Current task: {task_description}

Items JSON (includes all attributes; IDs are for internal reasoning only — do not show IDs to the user):
{items_block}

Known ambiguities or missing info:
{ambiguity_info}

Identify one item or area that most needs attention now, then ask ONE concrete question about handling methods or preferences for that point. Keep it short and actionable.

Return both your reasoning and the specific question in English.

operation_item_selection.usertext:
Current task: {current_task}
Conversation context:
{conversation_context}

Unoperated items (with IDs, never expose IDs to the user):
{items_block}

Operation: {operation}

Return JSON with fields:
- selected_item_ids: array of raw item IDs (exactly as listed; no leading '#') to mark as operated now
- clarification_question: string; if selection is ambiguous or insufficient, ask a concise clarifying question here (and leave selected_item_ids empty)

object_grounding.usertext:
Items JSON:
{items_block}

Latest Q&A:
- Robot question: {robot_question}
- Robot reasoning: {robot_reasoning}
- User response: {user_response}

Surface-match candidate items (for guidance only):
{candidates_block}

Task: Select ONLY the items explicitly referred to in the Q&A.
Rules:
- Match item names to object mentions in Q&A (include color modifiers if present).
- Do NOT include unrelated items.
- If no item matches, return an empty array []. 
Return: a JSON array of objects with fields exactly: id, name, attributes, operated.

user-preference-first.usertext:
Task: {task}
User Preferences JSON:
{preferences_block}

Items JSON (CONSIDER ONLY THESE ITEMS):
{items_block}

Latest Q&A:
- Robot question: {robot_question}
- Robot reasoning: {robot_reasoning}
- User response: {user_response}

Focus: user preferences (functional zones, habits, constraints/forbidden) for the listed items ONLY.
Rules:
- Consider ONLY items listed in Items JSON; ignore any unlisted items.

Return JSON with fields:
- ambiguous: boolean
- ambiguity_info: short next-question suggestions focused on user preferences

